quran[20]{c,v,t,f}:
  44,40,"Indeed, the Day of Decision is the appointed time for them all—"
  44,41,"a day when no patron will avail a protégé in any way, and they cannot be supported,"
  44,42,"except for one upon whom Allah has had{1}mercy; indeed, He is the Almighty, the Bestower of mercy.",footnotes:1:Frequently the Qur’an addresses the events of the Hereafter in past tense; this grammatical shift should be pondered by the reader.
  44,43,"Indeed, the Tree of Zaqqum{1}",footnotes:1:Trees in Hell which produce hot, bitter, rotten fruit.
  44,44,"<span class=""h"">is the food of the sinful one,</span>"
  44,45,"<span class=""h"">like molten brass boiling<sup foot_note=""81130"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>in the bellies"
  44,46,"like the boiling of scalding water."
  44,47,"“Take<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>him and drag him into the midst of Hell,"
  44,48,"then pour over his head some of the punishment of scalding water!”"
  44,49,"<span class=""h"">“Taste</span><a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a><span class=""h"">! You<sup foot_note=""81131"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>—indeed you—are the mighty, the noble{2}.",footnotes:2:This is said in sarcasm.
  44,50,"Indeed, this is what you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>were{1}skeptical about.”",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from singular to plural.
  44,51,"Indeed, the mindful<i class=""s"">(of God) </i>are in a safe domicile,"
  44,52,"amidst Gardens and springs,"
  44,53,"dressed in silk and brocade, facing one another."
  44,54,"So it is. And We married<a class=""sup""><sup>a </sup></a>them to spouses with lovely wide eyes."
  44,55,"They call therein for every kind of fruit, feeling safe."
  44,56,"Therein they do not taste death beyond the first death, and He{1}shielded them from the punishment of Hell—",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from 1st person to 3rd person.
  44,57,"a grace from your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord; that is the great triumph."
  44,58,"Thus have We made it{1}easy through your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>tongue, that they may remind themselves.",footnotes:1:The Qur’an.
  44,59,"So wait and watch<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>. Indeed, they too are waiting and watching."
